projects.title: Credit Card Fraud Detection using Random Forest Algorithm
projects.description: Goals: To detect fraudulent transactions in credit card data To prevent unauthorized transactions and protect customers from financial loss To improve the accuracy and speed of detecting fraudulent transactions.This project addresses the pressing issue of increasing credit card fraud in the modern technological landscape. Focusing specifically on real-world credit card transactions, the initiative involves the collection, analysis, and processing of a credit card dataset. Leveraging the Random Forest algorithm, the project aims to accurately identify instances of fraudulent transactions. Evaluation metrics, including accuracy, sensitivity, specificity, and precision, are employed to assess the performance of the techniques used. The project concludes with a notable achievement of approximately 99% accuracy in detecting fraudulent transactions, signifying the potential efficacy of the applied methods in bolstering security measures against evolving fraud tactics.
